@startuml
title C4 Level 2 - Container Diagram (NAPCORE Helpdesk)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 12
skinparam rectangle {
  BorderColor #2B5FAB
  FontColor #1F2F4A
  BackgroundColor #F8FBFF
}
skinparam actor {
  BorderColor #2B5FAB
  FontColor #1F2F4A
  BackgroundColor #EAF2FF
}

actor "PTO" as PTO
actor "PTA" as PTA
actor "Developer" as DEV
actor "ITS System Integrator" as INTEGRATOR
actor "Ticketing Agent" as TICKET

rectangle "NAPCORE Helpdesk" as SYSTEM {
  rectangle "Web GUI\n(Container)" as GUI #EAF2FF
  rectangle "Question API / Orchestrator\n(Container)\nFAQ-first, then RAG fallback" as API #DCE9FF
  rectangle "Controller LLM Service\n(Container)\nIntent + routing + SPARQL planning" as CONTROLLER #F0F6FF
  rectangle "FAQ Service\n(Container)\nApproved FAQ lookup + versions" as FAQ #F0F6FF
  rectangle "Retrieval Service\n(Container)\nEmbedding + vector search" as RETRIEVAL #F0F6FF
  rectangle "Narration LLM Service\n(Container)\nAnswer composition from evidence" as NARRATION #F0F6FF
  rectangle "Policy Guardrails Service\n(Container)\nSPARQL allowlist + citation + abstention" as GUARDRAILS #F0F6FF
  rectangle "Editorial Workflow Service\n(Container)\nDraft/Review/Approve/Publish" as EDITORIAL #F0F6FF
  database "PostgreSQL\n(Data Store)\nFAQ, events, evidence links" as PG #EEF5FF
  database "Vector Index\n(Data Store)\nSource chunk embeddings" as VDB #EEF5FF
  database "Semantic Graph Store\n(Data Store)\nGraphDB ontology + alignments" as SDB #EEF5FF
  rectangle "Ingestion Worker\n(Container)\nSync + chunk + index" as INGEST #F0F6FF
}

rectangle "Approved GitHub Repositories" as GITHUB
rectangle "Controller Model Runtime" as CONTROLLER_LLM
rectangle "Narration Model Runtime" as NARRATION_LLM

PTO --> GUI : Ask questions
PTA --> GUI : Ask questions
DEV --> GUI : Ask questions
INTEGRATOR --> GUI : Ask questions
TICKET --> GUI : Ask questions

' Top layer: actors arranged horizontally
PTO -[hidden]right-> PTA
PTA -[hidden]right-> DEV
DEV -[hidden]right-> INTEGRATOR
INTEGRATOR -[hidden]right-> TICKET

' Bottom layer: external systems below SYSTEM
SYSTEM -[hidden]down-> GITHUB
GITHUB -[hidden]right-> CONTROLLER_LLM
CONTROLLER_LLM -[hidden]right-> NARRATION_LLM

GUI --> API : Submit question
API --> CONTROLLER : Intent/routing/query planning
API --> FAQ : FAQ path when selected
API --> RETRIEVAL : Retrieval path when selected
API --> NARRATION : Compose grounded answer
API --> GUARDRAILS : Validate plans and answers
API --> EDITORIAL : Route low-confidence\nor flagged answers
API --> PG : Store question events\nand outcomes

CONTROLLER --> CONTROLLER_LLM : Run controller prompt
CONTROLLER --> GUARDRAILS : SPARQL/tool policy preflight
CONTROLLER --> RETRIEVAL : Provide retrieval constraints
CONTROLLER --> SDB : Constrained SPARQL queries\nwhen enabled
FAQ --> PG : Read/write FAQ entries\nand versions
RETRIEVAL --> VDB : Query top-k chunks
RETRIEVAL --> SDB : Graph-aware concept expansion\n(SPARQL) when enabled
RETRIEVAL --> PG : Log retrieval events
NARRATION --> NARRATION_LLM : Generate from evidence pack only
NARRATION --> GUARDRAILS : Citation and policy checks
NARRATION --> PG : Write answer + citations + confidence
GUARDRAILS --> PG : Write policy outcomes\nand abstention reasons
EDITORIAL --> PG : Store review decisions
INGEST --> GITHUB : Pull allowlisted sources
INGEST --> VDB : Upsert embeddings
INGEST --> SDB : Load ontology and\nalignment artifacts
INGEST --> PG : Store source metadata

note bottom of API
Decision policy:
1) Controller selects FAQ or RAG route.
2) RAG route executes retrieval and graph expansion when enabled.
3) Narration composes answer from evidence pack only.
4) Guardrails enforce SPARQL/source/citation policy, else abstain.
end note

note right of NARRATION_LLM
Top layer: Users.
Bottom layer: Approved source repositories and model runtimes.
end note

@enduml
